&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Activate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Activate is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit dedicated to turning scientific discoveries into real-world impact. Through partnerships with government, philanthropy, universities, and industry, Activate builds the cross-sector ecosystem that drives hard tech innovation—equipping scientists and engineers with world-class resources, training, and community to bring their work from discovery to deployment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since 2015, Activate&#39;s flagship fellowship has supported nearly 300 fellows across the United States, who have launched more than 230 companies and secured over $5.5 billion in follow-on funding. Now expanding beyond its flagship program, Activate is reaching scientists and engineers at more stages of their entrepreneurial journey across the world—multiplying the pathways from innovation to commercialization. Learn more at&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://activate.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt; Activate.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fellowship Manager, Anywhere serves as the program lead for the hybrid Activate Anywhere community, which supports fellows located across the United States. In this role, you will work closely with deep-tech science entrepreneurs throughout their two-year Activate fellowship journey, as they build world-changing technologies in fields like climate tech, biomanufacturing, and aerospace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fellowship Manager, Anywhere, is responsible for the Anywhere community’s fellowship experience—designing virtual programming and directing quarterly in-person gatherings—while overseeing operational excellence, including fellow recruitment &amp;amp; selection, benefits management, and program evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each Activate community supports about 20 fellows and is run by a three-person team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Fellowship Manager (this role) leads the local community, and reports to the Fellowship Director, who oversees all five US communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Fellowship Associate reports to the Fellowship Manager and is responsible for the community’s daily operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Managing Director is an experienced entrepreneur who mentors the community’s fellows and leads external ecosystem efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All three roles sit within the Fellowship team, and benefit from being on a team of peers performing similar work in other communities. This role is one of 5 Fellowship Managers at Activate, each responsible for one of our US communities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct Anywhere community programming, including bi-weekly virtual programming and quarterly in-person trips.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage local program operations, including fellow selection, fellow onboarding, fellow data, and fellow benefits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate a supportive, tight-knit community experience for Anywhere fellows, building strong individual relationships to coordinate necessary support and resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Fellowship Associate to ensure high-performance execution of local community operations and support their professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee community budgeting, strategy, team meetings, and team-wide coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to translate fellowship insights and stories into strategies that amplify organizational impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to broader Fellowship team-wide initiatives, operations, and cross-functional working groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Activate at virtual recruitment events and engage Anywhere alumni to strengthen community connections.&lt;/li&g

