&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Activate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Activate is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit dedicated to turning scientific discoveries into real-world impact. Through partnerships with government, philanthropy, universities, and industry, Activate builds the cross-sector ecosystem that drives hard tech innovation—equipping scientists and engineers with world-class resources, training, and community to bring their work from discovery to deployment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since 2015, Activate&#39;s flagship fellowship has supported nearly 300 fellows across the United States, who have launched more than 230 companies and secured over $5.5 billion in follow-on funding. Now expanding beyond its flagship program, Activate is reaching scientists and engineers at more stages of their entrepreneurial journey across the world—multiplying the pathways from innovation to commercialization. Learn more at&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://activate.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt; Activate.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Activate is seeking an Operations Intern to support the execution of the application and selection process for our next cohort of fellows. Working closely with the Pipeline team and Fellowship team members across Activate&#39;s five U.S. communities, this intern will help administer our application system, support applicants throughout the application process, and help organize data related to the Cohort 2027 selection process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Operations Intern will help implement the Cohort 2027 fellow selection process by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the team in external and internal communications with applicants, reviewers, and other stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organizing and analyzing information for the team related to the Activate fellow selection process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Testing and troubleshooting the application portal to ensure a seamless experience for applicants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documenting the procedures and workflows of the selection process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drafting and organizing training materials for team members and external reviewers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring and evaluating selection data using Activate’s systems and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate…&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has top-notch organizational skills and is highly detail-oriented.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can multitask and manage several complex projects at once using project management software such as Asana.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is comfortable with data management, including data visualization and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is comfortable with data management systems and tools, such as Google Suite, Airtable, and/or Survey Monkey Apply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is a team player who is also able to accomplish tasks independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a collaborative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is interested in supporting scientists to bring their tech to market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 40-hour per week paid internship running from&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;August 1, 2026 - December 15, 2026&lt;/strong&gt; with a pay rate of $23.00/hour. The role is open to U.S.-based candidates, with a preference for those located in the Bay Area (CA), Boston (MA), New York (NY), or Houston (TX), though remote work is available.&lt;/p&gt;
